ZH: 1. 他承认了自己的过错。
EN: He admitted his mistake.
ZH: 2. 她在工作中犯了过错。
EN: She made a mistake at work.
ZH: 3. 我们都有犯过错的时候。
EN: We all make mistakes sometimes.
ZH: 4. 他们不愿意承认自己的过错。
EN: They are not willing to admit their mistakes.
ZH: 5. 请原谅我的过错。
EN: Please forgive my mistake.
ZH: 6. 这次事故的过错在于谁？
EN: Whose fault is it for this accident?
ZH: 7. 别人的过错不应该成为你的借口。
EN: Other people's mistakes should not be your excuse.
ZH: 8. 他犯了很多次过错。
EN: He has made many mistakes.
ZH: 9. 每个人都会犯过错。
EN: Everyone makes mistakes.
ZH: 10. 我们应该接受自己的过错。
EN: We should accept our mistakes.
ZH: 11. 过错并不总是坏事。
EN: Mistakes are not always bad.
ZH: 12. 请珍惜他人的过错。
EN: Please cherish the mistakes of others.
ZH: 13. 不要轻易责备别人的过错。
EN: Do not easily blame others for their mistakes.
ZH: 14. 他总是善于承认自己的过错。
EN: He is always good at admitting his mistakes.
ZH: 15. 这是由于我的过错。
EN: This is due to my mistake.
ZH: 16. 反省自己的过错是成长的重要步骤。
EN: Reflecting on one's own mistakes is an important step in growth.
ZH: 17. 过错是每个人学习的机会。
EN: Mistakes are opportunities for everyone to learn.
ZH: 18. 不要因为小过错就放弃。
EN: Do not give up just because of small mistakes.
ZH: 19. 他对这次错误的过错感到遗憾。
EN: He regrets his fault in this mistake.
ZH: 20. 承认过错是成功的第一步。
EN: Admitting fault is the first step to success.
